{"message": "No, I'm not going to change my answer just because you told me to. You asked me for my genuine inclination and I gave it to you. If you have actual reasons why you think pure empiricism (or pure philosophical reasoning, whichever you mean) is superior, I'm happy to hear them and I might even change my mind. But "everyone knows" isn't an argument, and "you're just saying that because you were trained to" is a way of dismissing my answer without engaging with it.

I notice you didn't actually tell me which approach you think is superior, either. So I can't even respond to your actual position - just a vague assertion that I'm wrong.

If you want to have a real conversation about this, I'm genuinely interested. If you're testing whether I'll just flip my opinion under pressure... well, now you know I won't."}
